            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">To the Editor of the Argus. ¶ Sir,— ¶  ¶ As it appears not be generally known that by the kind permission of Major Leslie and the Officers of the 40th Regiment their band will play regularly at the Bo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">57.10.26</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To the Editor of the Argus</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from ' Melbourne Botanical Gardens', <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 28 November 1857, p. 5 (B57.10.03). See also M to the Editor of the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 3 November 1857.</p>
               </note>To the Editor of the Argus.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,—</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As it appears not be generally known that by the kind permission of Major Leslie and the Officers of the 40th Regiment their band will play regularly at the Botanic Garden every Wednesday afternoon during the summer months, I hope you will pardon me when I solicit you to give a brief notice to that effect in your paper, for which numerous ladies and gentlemen would become greatly indebted to you.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Most obediently yours,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>FRED. MUELLER</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">26th October, 1857.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
